From: Specula <specula@example.com>
Subject: [PATCH] libgomp: Set BAR_TASK_PENDING in omp_fulfill_event for unshackled threads

When omp_fulfill_event is called from an unshackled (non-OpenMP) thread
for a detached task with no dependent tasks (new_tasks == 0), the code
calls gomp_team_barrier_wake to wake a barrier thread but does not set
BAR_TASK_PENDING on bar->generation.

The barrier wait loop uses BAR_TASK_PENDING as the sole gate for entering
gomp_barrier_handle_tasks.  Without it set, the woken thread sees no
change in bar->generation and goes back to futex_wait.  Since
gomp_barrier_handle_tasks is the only path that calls
gomp_team_barrier_done (which completes the barrier when task_count == 0),
this results in a deadlock: all team threads sleep in the barrier and
nobody ever completes it.

The fix adds gomp_team_barrier_set_task_pending before the wake, matching
the pattern already used in the new_tasks > 0 path (added in commit
ba886d0c) and in gomp_target_task_completion.

Affects all three barrier implementations (centralized, flat/NVIDIA, POSIX)
since all use the same BAR_TASK_PENDING gating pattern.

libgomp/ChangeLog:

	* task.c (omp_fulfill_event): Call gomp_team_barrier_set_task_pending
	before waking barrier thread in unshackled-thread path when
	new_tasks == 0.

---
 libgomp/task.c | 13 ++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/libgomp/task.c b/libgomp/task.c
index e2d7f21..1ea4ed4 100644
--- a/libgomp/task.c
+++ b/libgomp/task.c
@@ -2754,9 +2754,16 @@ omp_fulfill_event (omp_event_handle_t event)
       && !do_wake
       && team->task_detach_count == 0
       && gomp_team_barrier_waiting_for_tasks (&team->barrier))
-    /* Ensure that at least one thread is woken up to signal that the
-       barrier can finish.  */
-    do_wake = 1;
+    {
+      /* Ensure that at least one thread is woken up to signal that the
+	 barrier can finish.  Set BAR_TASK_PENDING so the woken thread
+	 enters gomp_barrier_handle_tasks to discover task_count == 0
+	 and call gomp_team_barrier_done.  Without this, the futex_wake
+	 alone does not change bar->generation, so the woken thread sees
+	 no change and goes back to sleep -- deadlock.  */
+      gomp_team_barrier_set_task_pending (&team->barrier);
+      do_wake = 1;
+    }

   /* If we are running in an unshackled thread, the team might vanish before
      gomp_team_barrier_wake is run if we release the lock first, so keep the
